<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-11-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="808" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d808">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Eddy</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-11-02"><hi rend="italic">November 2,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Eddy reports that according to a proclamation just issued the
                            departments of the army, navy, and the imperial domain will not come
                            under the jurisdiction of the new parliament. Under another proclamation
                            all political prisoners not deemed dangerous to the state will be
                            released. Reports of the gravest character have been received from
                            Odessa.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>